# SciGate Agent Rules

## JSON Contract
Agent 1 outputs: `{ domain, scores: {env, seeds, data, docs, total}, grade, fixes: [{rank, title, files, dimension, points_recoverable, claude_fix_hint}], gate_blocked, gate_threshold }`

## Fix Generation
- `build_skill_context(domain, fix)` constructs Claude system prompt per-fix
- Always strip markdown fences from Claude response before JSON.parse
- Safety filter: never write to files matching train/model/loss/network/arch/backbone/head/encoder/decoder

## Seed Templates
- ML: torch.manual_seed + cuda.manual_seed_all + cudnn.deterministic
- Bio: set.seed(42) in R
- General: random.seed + np.random.seed

## Path Fixes
Replace `/home/...` or `/mnt/...` with:
`os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__)), '..', 'data', filename)`

## GitLab Flow
- Agent models: Sonnet for audit/fix, Haiku for memory (fast + cheap)
- Timeouts: audit 120-180s, fix 300s, memory 60s
- MR branch naming: `scigate/fix-{sha[:8]}`
- Always open MR as draft with labels: scigate, reproducibility
